Title: Chiheisen no Mukō e (地平線の向こうへ / Beyond the Horizon)

[Genre: Epic Math Rock / Cinematic Folk Rock / Anime OP]
[Tempo: 96 BPM, with tempo shifts in bridge]
[Key: D Minor, modulating to F Major in final chorus]
[Vocal: Female, powerful and versatile; clear, soaring highs; intimate, whispered lows]
[Mood: Epic, spiritual, triumphant, nostalgic, uniting tradition with modern glory]

Instrumentation Key (for audio engine)
Flute: Wooden flute, airy and rich (like bansuri)

Large Drum: Deep, resonant drum with a heavy, booming tone (like dhimay)

Small Hand Cymbals: Bright, rhythmic metallic percussion (like jhyali)

Frame Drum: Shallow drum with a sharp, slapping attack (like damphu)

Electric Guitar: Clean arpeggios and distorted power chords

Acoustic Guitar: Fingerpicked, warm tones

Bass Guitar: Deep, driving

Drums: Full kit with toms and cymbals

Orchestral Strings: Sweeping, cinematic

Synth Pads: Ambient, atmospheric

[INTRO]

[A single Large Drum beats slowly, like a heartbeat. A Flute plays a solemn, ascending melody, echoing in an open space. The sound of wind and distant chimes. A Frame Drum enters with a sharp, rhythmic pattern, joined by Small Hand Cymbals playing a bright, syncopated rhythm. Acoustic Guitar begins a fingerpicked arpeggio, shimmering. The Flute repeats the melody, now layered with Electric Guitar playing a clean, sustained chord.]

